{"vocabInfos":[{"lsjDefs":"<b> χάος</b> [ᾰ], εος, <br /> <i>Attic dialect</i> ους, τό, <b>chaos,</b> the first state of the universe, πρώτιστα χ. γένετ᾽, αὐτὰρ ἔπειτα Γαῖ᾽ εὐρύστερνος κτλ. [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 8th-7th c.BC: Hesiodus Epicus “Theogonia” 116, compare 6th c.BC: Ibycus Lyricus 28, 5th c.BC: Epicharmus Comicus 170.3, 5th c.BC: Acusilaus Historicus “fragment” 5J., 4th c.BC: Aristoteles Philosophus “Metaphysica” 1091b6, 5th-6th c.BC: Aristophanes Comicus “Aves” 693 (_anapaest meter_); χάους.. παῖς καλεῦμαι 3rd c.BC: Simmias “Alae” 7 \">Refs 8th c.BC+</a>]; represented sometimes as <b>infinite space,</b> [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 2nd c.AD: Sextus Empiricus Philosophus “Πυρρώνειοι ὑποτυπώσεις” 3.121, compare 3rd c.AD: Plotinus Philosophus 6.8.11 \">Refs 2nd c.AD+</a>]; sometimes as <b>unformed matter,</b> [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 2nd c.AD: Lucianus Sophista “Am.” 32 \">Refs 2nd c.AD+</a>] (especially, <i>accusative</i> to the Stoics, <b>water,</b> [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 4th-3rd c.BC: Zeno Citieus Stoicus 1.29 (with derivation from χέω)). \">Refs 4th c.BC+</a>]<br /><Level3><b>__2</b></Level3> <b>space, the expanse of air,</b> ἄτρυτον χ. [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 5th c.BC: Bacchylides Lyricus 5.27, compare 5th-6th c.BC: Aristophanes Comicus “Nubes” 424 (_anapaest meter_), 627, “Av.” 1218. \">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>]<br /><Level4><b>__2.b</b></Level4> τὸ χ. τοῦ ἐφ᾽ ἑκάτερα ἀπείρου αἰῶνος, of <b>infinite</b> time, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 2nd c.AD: Marcus Antoninus Imperator 4.3. \">Refs 2nd c.AD+</a>]<br /><Level3><b>__3</b></Level3> <b>the nether abyss, infinite darkness,</b> joined with Ἔρεβος, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 5th-6th c.BC: Plato Philosophus “Axiochus” 371e \">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>]; with ὄρφνη, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 4th c.AD(?): Quintus Smyrnaeus Epicus 2.614 \">Refs 4th c.AD+</a>]; represented as in the interior of the globe, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 1st-2nd c.AD: Plutarchus Biographus et Philosophus 2.953a\">Refs 1st c.AD+</a>]; χάους κύνα, of Cerberus, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" “APl.” 4.91. \">Refs</a>]<br /><Level4><b>__3.b</b></Level4> generally, <b>darkness,</b> [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 3rd c.BC: Apollonius Rhodius Epicus 4.1697. \">Refs 3rd c.BC+</a>]<br /><Level3><b>__4</b></Level3> <b>any vast gulf</b> or <b>chasm,</b> [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" LXX.Mic.1.6, LXX.Zech.14.4 \">LXX</a>]; of a <b>pit,</b> [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 3rd c.AD: Oppianus Apamensis Epicus “Cynegetica” 4.92 \">Refs 3rd c.AD+</a>]; of the <b>gaping jaws</b> of the crocodile, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\"[prev. work] 3.414, compare 4.161, “H.” 5.52. \">Refs</a>]<br /><Level3><b>__5</b></Level3> [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 4th-5th c.BC: Pythagoras Philosophus \">Refs 4th c.BC+</a>] name for <b>one,</b> [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" Theol.Ar. 6. \">Refs</a>]","strongNumber":"G9698","accentedUnicode":"χάος","shortDef":"chaos","mediumDef":"chaos","stepGloss":"chaos","stepTransliteration":"chaos","_step_Type":"word"}]}